“This event was presented by the Grade 1 and 2’s as a fundraiser for upgrading the senior changing rooms,” said school spokeswoman Sonja Holtzhausen.      “It’s one of the school’s biggest fundraisers and all the grades get a turn.” All the participants waited anxiously at the starting point. After two false starts due to great enthusiasm and excitement, participants took the route around the school. As far as they went, they threw colorful powder paint in the air. 